@startuml
' Small Business Core Systems Operating Model
' Diagram purpose: show core business systems, handoffs, SOP/tooling layer, and KPI improvement loop.

!include ../../../../../tooling/styles/plantuml/structural/package-diagram-style.iuml

title Small Business Core Systems Operating Model

package "Demand Creation" {
  rectangle "Marketing and\nLead Generation" as Marketing
  rectangle "Sales and\nLead Conversion" as Sales
}

package "Value Delivery" {
  rectangle "Operations and\nFulfillment" as Ops
  rectangle "Customer\nExperience" as CX
}

package "Business Control" {
  rectangle "Financial\nManagement" as Finance
  rectangle "Administration and\nIT Security" as AdminIT
  rectangle "HR and People\nManagement" as HR
}

rectangle "Leadership and\nStrategy" as Leadership
rectangle "SOP and Tooling\nLayer" as SOPTools
rectangle "KPI and Continuous\nImprovement Layer" as KPI

Marketing --> Sales : qualified leads\nsource context
Sales --> Ops : closed-won handoff\nscope and commitments
Ops --> CX : product or service\ndelivery
Ops --> Finance : delivery milestones\nbilling evidence
Sales --> Finance : bookings\nforecast
HR --> AdminIT : onboarding and\noffboarding triggers
AdminIT --> Marketing : tools, documents,\naccess, backups
AdminIT --> Sales
AdminIT --> Ops
AdminIT --> Finance
Leadership --> Marketing : goals and positioning
Leadership --> Sales : revenue targets
Leadership --> Ops : capacity priorities
Leadership --> Finance : budget and cash priorities
Leadership --> HR : workforce plan

SOPTools ..> Marketing : repeatable work
SOPTools ..> Sales
SOPTools ..> Ops
SOPTools ..> Finance
SOPTools ..> AdminIT
SOPTools ..> HR
SOPTools ..> Leadership

Marketing ..> KPI : campaign metrics
Sales ..> KPI : conversion metrics
Ops ..> KPI : delivery metrics
Finance ..> KPI : cash and margin metrics
AdminIT ..> KPI : reliability and security metrics
HR ..> KPI : people capacity metrics
KPI --> Leadership : scorecard, trends,\nrisks, decisions
Leadership --> SOPTools : improvement priorities\nand operating standards

note right of SOPTools
SOPs define triggers, owners,
steps, evidence, and escalation.
Tools support the SOP; they do
not replace process ownership.
end note

note bottom of KPI
The improvement loop converts
KPI gaps into prioritized actions,
updated SOPs, tooling changes,
and leadership decisions.
end note

@enduml
